    "description": [
        {
            "text": "$\\textit{Voltage}$, also referred to as $\\textit{Electric Tension}$, is the difference between electrical potentials of two points. For an electric field within a medium, $U_{ab} = - \\int_{r_a}^{r_b} E . {dr}$, where $E$ is electric field strength.\nFor an irrotational electric field, the voltage is independent of the path between the two points $a$ and $b$.",
            "lang": "en"
        }
    ],
